{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01HepXgXQPefhSwFgbsSi1i6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the knowledge file against the source file carefully.\n\nLooking at the source RST file and comparing it to the knowledge file.\n\n**V1: Omission Check**\n\nSource sections:\n1. Title + class name (s1 in knowledge)\n2. 概要 (s2 in knowledge)\n3. Template methods table + code block (s3 in knowledge)\n4. ハンドラ処理フロー (s4 in knowledge)\n\nLet me go through each section carefully:\n\n**Section: Template methods (s3)**\n\nSource code block:\n```java\nRequestMessage   req;\nResponseMessage  res; \n\n\nExecutionContext ctx;\n\nreq = receive();                // (フレームワークが要求電文を受信)\n\ntry {\n    if ( usesAutoRead() ) {\n        req.readRecord();       // 要求電文のデータ部からデータレコードを自動的に読み込む。\n                                // (主にシングルレコード形式の電文で使用する。)\n    }\n\n    res = onReceive(req, ctx);  // 要求電文毎に呼ばれる。\n    commit();                   // (フレームワークが業務トランザクションを\n```\n\nContinuing with the template method flow...\n\n} catch(e) {\n    rollback();                 // (業務トランザクションをロールバックする。)\n    res = onError(e, req, ctx); // 業務処理で例外が発生し、業務トランザクションが\n                                // ロールバックされた直後に呼ばれる。\n                                // エラー応答電文をリターンして返す。\n} finally {\n    send(res);                  // (フレームワークが応答電文を送信)\n}\n\nI'm describing the request-response processing flow where the framework receives a request, optionally auto-reads record data, invokes the business logic handler, and commits the transaction. If an exception occurs, it rolls back and calls the error handler, then sends the response back in the finally block. I'm noticing the knowledge file strips away the try-catch-finally structure entirely, presenting the code as a flat sequence with comments instead of showing how `commit()` lives in the try block, `rollback()` and `onError()` are in the catch, and `send(res)` always executes in